\nto 2006, this event had a larger peak IR flux and similar submillimeter flux,\nbut it lacked measurable X-ray emission. It also showed a shorter delay between\nthe IR and submillimeter peaks. Based on these events we propose a synchrotron\nand self-Compton model to relate the submillimeter lag and the variable\nIR/X-ray luminosity ratio.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Dec 2007 05:00:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Jul 2008 22:32:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-09-21"}
